<a name="1661"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Note on Kael armor vs. Skyshrine armor</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Sirensa on Friday, April 27 @ 12:48:49 EDT<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Sirensa">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td><blockquote>"Kael armor tends to be higher ac, higher hp, and usually better resists."</blockquote>
This is not always the case as evidenced below...
<br>
<br>
<i>Note this is not a complete sample, but all of the below comparisons show Skyshrine quested armor having better resists and higher hps, except for warrior which comes in close 550hp versus 521 for skyshrine when you calculate the stamina bonus</i>
<br>
<br>
<b>For a complete set of Cleric Armor:</b>
<br>
<br>
Kael: 237ac, 240hp, 255mana, 24str, 13sta, 37wis, 7cha, 5pr, 22mr, 8dr, 11fr, 9cr.
<br>
<br>
Skyshrine:  209ac, 305hp, 315mana, 10str, 35sta, 5agi, 3dex, 51wis, 9cha, 14pr, 22mr, 17dr, 12fr, 25cr.
<br>
<br>
<b>For a complete set of Druid Armor:</b>
<br>
<br>
Kael:  101ac, 80hp, 275mana, 6str, 2sta, 15agi, 11dex, 53wis, 4pr, 19mr, 7dr, 9fr, 9cr.
<br>
<br>
Skyshrine:  74ac, 160hp, 370mana, 8str, 16sta, 6agi, 20dex, 59wis, 22pr, 29mr, 10dr, 11fr, 13cr.
<br>
<br>
<b>For a complete set of Paladin Armor:</b>
<br>
<br>
Kael:  237ac, 140hp, 140mana, 43str, 21sta, 10agi, 15dex, 34wis, 3pr, 16mr, 6dr, 3fr, 5cr.
<br>
<br>
Skyshrine:  206ac, 270hp, 90mana, 37str, 43sta, 15agi, 28dex, 32wis, 9pr, 28mr, 12dr, 7fr, 9cr.
<br>
<br>
<b>For a complete set of Warrior Armor:</b>
<br>
<br>
Kael:  279ac, 310hp, 34str, 40sta, 23agi, 17dex, 2pr, 16mr, 4dr, 9fr, 14cr.
<br>
<br>
Skyshrine:  250ac, 335hp, 36str, 31sta, 39agi, 42dex, 1pr, 25mr, 11dr, 18fr, 17cr.
<br>
<br>
<b>For a complete set of Ranger Armor:</b>
<br>
<br>
Kael:  203ac, 130hp, 140mana, 35str, 15sta, 13agi, 27dex, 30wis, 3pr, 15mr, 6dr, 3fr, 6cr.
<br>
<br>
Skyshrine:  176ac, 240hp, 100mana, 49str, 29sta, 12agi, 29dex, 24wis, 10pr, 26mr, 8dr, 10fr, 10cr.
<br>
<br>
<i>Clearly not everyone might not wear a complete set of each armor, but if you are going for pure hp, resists, mana (for priest,int casters), the Skyshrine armor is clearly superior.
<br>
<br>
Also, Being aligned with Dragons does not mean that never kill CoV allied mobs.  Being in extreme warmly for faction gives the option to pick and choose which dragons we would like to kill.  Same way that many giant allied guilds kill the Statue of Rallos Zek.</i>
<br>
<br>
~Sirensa</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1663&sid=191&pid=1661&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1663">Also regarding faction..</a> by Valdayana-Quellious <font size=2>on Friday, April 27 @ 13:43:50 EDT</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1666&sid=191&pid=1663&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1666">Fair enough</a> by EdairNmirroz <font size=2>on Friday, April 27 @ 14:14:36 EDT</font><br><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1667&sid=191&pid=1663&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1667">Have to say...</a> by Jice-Virago <font size=2>on Saturday, April 28 @ 10:45:59 EDT</font><br></ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1664&sid=191&pid=1661&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1664">Re: Note on Kael armor vs. Skyshrine armor</a> by EdairNmirroz <font size=2>on Friday, April 27 @ 14:07:50 EDT</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1678&sid=191&pid=1664&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1678">Don't know if this is new or not, but....</a> by Jice-Virago <font size=2>on Monday, April 30 @ 03:34:25 EDT</font><br></ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1679&sid=191&pid=1661&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1679">Re: Note on Kael armor vs. Skyshrine armor</a> by Seolta_BotS <font size=2>on Monday, April 30 @ 04:04:12 EDT</font><br></ul></p><a name="1662"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Raising giant faction</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Llarn on Friday, April 27 @ 13:37:37 EDT<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Llarn">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>It is possible to raise all three giant factions without every laying hands on a dorf. I was severely KOS to all giants (our guild initially allied with them before seeing the light). When we went giant friendly I chose to keep my dorf faction because of the exclusive location of Velium bars (you can, in theory, mule this, but it's a pain in the ass to mule 5000 plat of bars weekly).<br>
<br>
Solution - kill in Skyshrine/WW until you are dubious to Kromzek. Then hand in dwarf heads, acquired with either a twink or by guildmates not keeping dwarf faction, to fix the other factions. Took me roughly 150 heads to become warmly (Kromzek)/amiable (Kromrif)/amiable (Tormax).<br>
<br>
There are a few other quests you can do to raise all three factions and only lower CoV, but I believe this is the fastest.<br>
<br>
Llarn, Officer of Prophecy<br>
L60 Enchanter, Bertoxxulous</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1676&sid=191&pid=1662&mode=thread&order=0&thold=#1676">Re: Raising giant faction</a> by Scotto <font size=2>on Monday, April 30 @ 02:04:33 EDT</font><br></ul></p></td><td bgcolor=ffffff><img src=themes/NukeNews/pixel.gif width=10 height=1 border=0></td></tr></table>

